      "message": "I started with sk_crash(), since a recorder should never need to fall into the device.\n\nHowever, we (for some reason) support this:\n\nSkCanvas canvas(10, 10);\n\nWhich isn\u0027t a recorder, but is supposed to not draw (and not crash). Hence the device draw methods *do* get called. So I replaced sk_crash() with function to document that the class wasn\u0027t incomplete, but deliberately wanted to not draw. Perhaps I should rename it do_not_draw() or draws_nothing().\n\nThat said, I don\u0027t feel strongly either way.",
